	<title>When We Loved Mussolini | Adam Tooze | The New York Review of Books</title>
	<meta name="description" content="America’s new power in the 1920s was based on its economy, and in the projection of an American vision of international order beyond the League of Nations, it was US bankers who led the way. The crucial issues of Italian–American diplomacy were not questions of democracy, but of finance." />
